protoActionableErr.description: `ActionableErr` defines an error that occurred along with an optional list of suggestions

protoBuildEvent.description:
`BuildEvent` describes the build status per artifact, and will be emitted by Skaffold anytime a build starts or finishes, successfully or not.
If the build fails, an error will be attached to the event.

additional.description: Additional key value pairs to describe the deploy pipeline

artifacts.description:
A map of `artifact name -> build-state`. Artifact name is defined in the `skaffold.yaml`. The `build-state` can be:
- `"Not started"`: not yet started
- `"In progress"`: build started
- `"Complete"`: build succeeded
- `"Failed"`: build failed

protoBuildState.description: `BuildState` maps Skaffold artifacts to their current build states

protoBuildType.description:
Enum indicating build type i.e. local, cluster vs GCB
- UNKNOWN_BUILD_TYPE: Could not determine Build Type
 - CLUSTER: Cluster Build
 - GCB: GCB Build
 - LOCAL: Local Build

protoBuilderType.description:
Enum indicating builders used
- UNKNOWN_BUILDER_TYPE: Could not determine builder type
 - JIB: JIB Builder
 - BAZEL: Bazel Builder
 - BUILDPACKS: Buildpacks Builder
 - CUSTOM: Custom Builder
 - KANIKO: Kaniko Builder
 - DOCKER: Docker Builder

protoClusterType.description:

- UNKNOWN_CLUSTER_TYPE: Could not determine Cluster Type
 - MINIKUBE: Minikube Cluster
 - GKE: GKE cluster

anytime a deployment starts or completes, successfully or not.

protoResourceStatusCheckEvent.description:
A Resource StatusCheck Event, indicates progress for each kubernetes deployment.
For every resource, there will be exactly one event with `status` *Succeeded* or *Failed* event.
There can be multiple events with `status` *Pending*.
Skaffold polls for resource status every 0.5 second. If the resource status changes, an event with `status` Pending, Complete and Failed
will be sent with the new status.

resources.description:

- `"In progress"`: InProgress is sent after every resource check is complete.
- `"Succeeded"`: - `"Failed"`:

protoSuggestion.description: Suggestion defines the action a user needs to recover from an error.

protoSuggestionCode.description:
Enum for Suggestion codes
- NIL: default nil suggestion.
This is usually set when no error happens.
 - ADD_DEFAULT_REPO: Add Default Repo
 - CHECK_DEFAULT_REPO: Verify Default Repo
 - CHECK_DEFAULT_REPO_GLOBAL_CONFIG: Verify default repo in the global config
 - GCLOUD_DOCKER_AUTH_CONFIGURE: run gcloud docker auth configure
 - DOCKER_AUTH_CONFIGURE: Run docker auth configure
 - CHECK_GCLOUD_PROJECT: Verify Gcloud Project
 - CHECK_DOCKER_RUNNING: Check if docker is running
 - FIX_USER_BUILD_ERR: Fix User Build Error
 - DOCKER_BUILD_RETRY: Docker build internal error, try again
 - FIX_CACHE_FROM_ARTIFACT_CONFIG: Fix `cacheFrom` config for given artifact and try again
 - FIX_SKAFFOLD_CONFIG_DOCKERFILE: Fix `dockerfile` config for a given artifact and try again.
 - FIX_JIB_PLUGIN_CONFIGURATION: Use a supported Jib plugin type
 - FIX_DOCKER_NETWORK_CONTAINER_NAME: Docker build network invalid docker container name (or id).
 - CHECK_DOCKER_NETWORK_CONTAINER_RUNNING: Docker build network container not existing in the current context.
 - CHECK_CLUSTER_CONNECTION: Check cluster connection
 - CHECK_MINIKUBE_STATUS: Check minikube status
 - INSTALL_HELM: Install helm tool
 - UPGRADE_HELM: Upgrade helm tool
 - FIX_SKAFFOLD_CONFIG_HELM_ARTIFACT_OVERRIDES: Fix helm `releases.artifactOverrides` config to match with `build.artiofacts`
 - UPGRADE_HELM32: Upgrade helm version to v3.2.0 and higher.
 - FIX_SKAFFOLD_CONFIG_HELM_CREATE_NAMESPACE: Set `releases.createNamespace` to false.
 - INSTALL_KUBECTL: Install kubectl tool
 - CHECK_CONTAINER_LOGS: Container run error
 - CHECK_READINESS_PROBE: Pod Health check error
 - CHECK_CONTAINER_IMAGE: Check Container image
 - ADDRESS_NODE_MEMORY_PRESSURE: Node pressure error
 - ADDRESS_NODE_DISK_PRESSURE: Node disk pressure error
 - ADDRESS_NODE_NETWORK_UNAVAILABLE: Node network unavailable error
 - ADDRESS_NODE_PID_PRESSURE: Node PID pressure error
 - ADDRESS_NODE_UNSCHEDULABLE: Node unschedulable error
 - ADDRESS_NODE_UNREACHABLE: Node unreachable error
 - ADDRESS_NODE_NOT_READY: Node not ready error
 - ADDRESS_FAILED_SCHEDULING: Scheduler failure error
 - CHECK_HOST_CONNECTION: Cluster Connectivity error
 - START_MINIKUBE: Minikube is stopped: use `minikube start`
 - UNPAUSE_MINIKUBE: Minikube is paused: use `minikube unpause`
 - RUN_DOCKER_PULL: Run Docker pull for the image with v1 manifest and try again.
 - SET_RENDER_FLAG_OFFLINE_FALSE: Rerun with correct offline flag value.
 - OPEN_ISSUE: Open an issue so this situation can be diagnosed
